# Root-level ignores for the Docker harness. backend/ and frontend/ keep their own .gitignore
# for their venv / node_modules. (gitignore has no inline comments — keep them on their own lines.)

# Secrets — never commit. `.env` matches only a file literally named .env, so also cover the
# deploy's `secrets.env` (and any *.env), plus key/cert material. The prod secrets file (signing
# key, OAuth secret, metrics token) lives only on the host, never in git.
.env
*.env
secrets.env
*.pem
*.key
*.keystore
id_rsa*
# Stray root node_modules (the app's real deps live in frontend/node_modules).
/node_modules
.DS_Store
# Visual-companion brainstorm mockups (superpowers) — local only, never commit.
.superpowers/
.gstack/
# Reference material — multi-MB papers + upstream chat UI starting point; kept local only.
/reference_material/
# Scratch eval metrics scratchpad — local only.
/eval_metrics.md
# Generated code-review artifacts — local only.
/docs/reviews/
# OpenCode local tool workspace - local only.
/.opencode/
# Submission email strategy notes — local only (untracked pre-invite; old versions remain in git history).
/docs/submission-email.md
